ide-of-kyiv-12566885','2022-03-15 20:19:00','2022-03-15 22:38:29'),(1491,51,2,1,NULL,'Marina Ovsyannikova: Journalist fined £210 after protest against Ukraine war on Russian state TV','During a live broadcast on Channel One on Monday evening, Marina Ovsyannikova, who is thought to have worked for the company for years, walked on to the set behind the presenter with a placard denouncing the country\'s invasion of Ukraine.','https://news.sky.com/story/ukraine-war-russian-journalist-marina-ovsyannikova-feared-missing-after-on-air-anti-war-protest-is-pictured-with-her-lawyer-12566880','2022-03-15 17:55:00','2022-03-15 22:39:09'),(1492,2,2,1,NULL,'Ukraine-Russia war latest: More than 3m have now fled Ukraine, says UN, as Czech, Polish and Slovenian leaders arrive for Zelenskiy meeting – live','The UN says it expects the number of Ukrainian refugees to reach at least four million, while Poland’s PM announced he and his counterparts from the Czech Republic and Slovenia are now in Kyiv','https://www.theguardian.com/world/live/2022/mar/15/ukraine-war-large-explosions-heard-in-kyiv-zelenskiy-calls-on-russian-troops-to-surrender-putin-china-latest-news','2022-03-15 22:34:00','2022-03-15 22:43:01'),(1493,2,2,1,NULL,'Ukraine will not join Nato, says Zelenskiy, as shelling of Kyiv continues','Ukraine’s president, Volodymyr Zelenskiy has acknowledged that Ukraine will not become a Nato member, in a significant concession on a day when Kyiv was pounded by Russian shells and missiles and the invading force tightened its grip on the capital.','https://www.theguardian.com/world/2022/mar/15/kyiv-facing-dangerous-moment-amid-signs-of-russias-tightening-grip','2022-03-15 19:02:00','2022-03-15 22:43:56'),(1494,2,2,1,NULL,'‘Her anger had been building’: Russian TV protester told friend of plan','The Russian television producer who staged an extraordinary anti-war protest live on national television on Monday night outlined her plan to a friend the day before, having become increasingly angry about the Russian invasion, the Guardian has learned.','https://www.theguardian.com/world/2022/mar/15/russia-tv-protest-marina-ovsyannikova-ukraine-war','2022-03-15 14:50:00','2022-03-15 22:44:43'),(1495,2,2,1,NULL,'Britain blocks luxury exports to Russia worth hundreds of millions','Russian oligarchs will no longer have access to baubles such as the cars, artworks and designer handbags sold by British companies, after the government blocked exports worth hundreds of millions of pounds.','https://www.theguardian.com/business/2022/mar/15/britain-blocks-luxury-exports-to-russia-worth-hundreds-of-millions','2022-03-15 19:39:00','2022-03-15 22:45:27'),(1496,2,2,1,NULL,'Polish, Czech and Slovenian prime ministers arrive in Kyiv','Volodymyr Zelenskiy told reporters “with allies like this we will win this war” after the prime ministers of Poland, the Czech Republic and Slovenia made a perilous train journey to Kyiv to offer their support.','https://www.theguardian.com/world/2022/mar/15/polish-czech-and-slovenian-prime-ministers-travel-to-kyiv-ukraine','2022-03-15 22:02:00','2022-03-15 22:46:09'),(1497,2,2,1,NULL,'Biden to visit Nato and EU in Brussels as pressure over Ukraine increases – as it happened','Joe Biden will travel to Brussels next week to meet with the leaders of the Nato alliance and the European Commission to discuss the Russian invasion of Ukraine.','https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/live/2022/mar/15/biden-us-ukraine-european-trip-latest-updates-politics-live','2022-03-15 21:09:00','2022-03-15 22:46:51'),(1498,2,2,1,NULL,'‘It’s the right thing to do’: the 300,000 volunteer hackers coming together to fight Russia','Ukraine appealed for a global army of IT experts to help in the battle against Putin – and many answered the call. We speak to people on the digital frontline','https://www.theguardian.com/world/2022/mar/15/volunteer-hackers-fight-russia','2022-03-15 10:00:00','2022-03-15 22:47:32'),(1499,2,2,1,NULL,'Russia-Ukraine war: what we know on day 20 of the Russian invasion','A series of Russian strikes hit a residential neighbourhood in the capital on Tuesday morning, igniting a huge fire and prompting a frantic rescue effort in a 15-storey apartment building.','https://www.theguardian.com/world/2022/mar/15/russia-ukraine-war-what-we-know-on-day-20-of-the-russian-invasion','2022-03-15 18:04:00','2022-03-15 22:48:55'),(1500,2,2,1,NULL,'What is a no-fly zone and could one be imposed over Ukraine?','Ukrainian president Volodymyr Zelenskiy again urged Nato on Monday to impose a no-fly zone over his country, saying it would protect not only Ukraine but the countries of the Atlantic alliance from Russian air attacks.','https://www.theguardian.com/world/2022/mar/15/what-is-a-no-fly-zone-and-could-one-be-imposed-over-ukraine','2022-03-15 02:14:00','2022-03-15 22:49:43'),(1501,8,2,1,NULL,'War in Ukraine: What happened on day 20 of Russia\'s invasion','On day 20 of Russia\'s invasion of Ukraine, residents in the capital Kyiv were placed under a 35-hour curfew - but that didn\'t stop the prime ministers of Poland, Slovenia and the Czech Republic from travelling there by train.','https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-60755202','2022-03-16 00:44:00','2022-03-15 22:52:16'),(1502,8,2,1,NULL,'Tens of thousands evacuated from Ukrainian cities','Russian troops are holding 400 people, including doctors and patients, \"like hostages\" inside a hospital in Mariupol, the deputy mayor says','https://www.bbc.com/news/live/world-europe-60746557','2022-03-15 00:37:00','2022-03-15 22:53:19'),(1503,8,2,1,NULL,'Ukraine war: Infection and hunger as hundreds hide in Mariupol cellar','The city is encircled by Russian troops and remains under constant bombardment with almost 400,000 people still trapped without running water, and food and medical supplies quickly running out.','https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-60736845','2022-03-15 17:54:00','2022-03-15 22:54:34'),(1504,8,2,1,NULL,'Ukraine war: Zelensky asks Canada\'s parliament to ‘Please close the sky\'','Speaking virtually from Ukraine to a packed crowd in the House of Commons to members of parliament, senators and dignitaries on Tuesday, Mr Zelensky thanked Canada - a \"steadfast supporter\"','https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-60752391','2022-03-15 20:55:00','2022-03-15 22:55:56'),(1505,5,2,1,NULL,'March 15 2022, Russia invades Ukraine','Fatalities were reported after shelling hit buildings in residential areas across Kyiv on Tuesday morning, according to Ukrainian authorities. A 35-hour curfew is now underway in the city as Russian forces continue their attacks.','https://edition.cnn.com/europe/live-news/ukraine-russia-putin-news-03-15-22/index.html','2022-03-16 00:48:00','2022-03-15 22:58:18'),(1506,5,2,1,NULL,'\'We all will be judged.\' Russian prisoners of war voice disquiet, shame over war in Ukraine','Russian President Vladimir Putin \"has given orders to commit crimes. It\'s not just to demilitarize Ukraine or defeat the Armed Forces of Ukraine, but now cities of peaceful civilians are being destroyed.\" ','https://edition.cnn.com/2022/03/15/europe/ukraine-russian-prisoners-of-war-intl/index.html','2022-03-15 21:21:00','2022-03-15 22:59:01');
